// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Secrets template — COMMITTED to the repo (safe; contains no real secrets).
//
// Setup:
//   1. cp Secrets.example.xcconfig Secrets.xcconfig   (Secrets.xcconfig is gitignored)
//   2. Deploy the Gemini proxy and set its secret — see
//      supabase/functions/gemini-proxy/README.md
//   3. Fill in the two values below in your Secrets.xcconfig
//
// The Gemini API key NO LONGER lives in the app — it lives only as a Supabase
// secret behind the `gemini-proxy` Edge Function. The app ships only these two
// (both non-secret: the anon key is public by design, gated by the function):
//
//   SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF -> Info.plist -> https://<ref>.supabase.co/functions/v1/gemini-proxy
//   SUPABASE_ANON_KEY    -> Info.plist -> sent as the `apikey` / Authorization header
//
// We store the project REF (not the full URL): xcconfig treats `//` in a value
// as a comment, so a pasted `https://…` URL would be silently truncated.
// Find both in the Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → General (Reference ID)
// and → API (anon public key).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF =
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY =

// Voice Isolation (Polish page) — ElevenLabs Voice Isolator API key.
// Get one at https://elevenlabs.io/app/settings/api-keys (10 free minutes on signup).
// Leave blank to build without isolation (the feature shows a friendly "add your key" error).
// NOTE: this currently ships in the binary for local testing; production should move it behind
// a proxy (Supabase Edge Function) like the Gemini key above.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY =
